==English==

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} [[consensus]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# [[General]] agreement among the members of a given group or community, each of which exercises some discretion in decision making and follow-up action.
# A specific method of [[community]] decision making where consent by all parties is required.
# Average projected value, as in the finance term consensus forecast.
# (Working definition) The lack of active opposition to a decision among key stakeholders.

